com.axibase.tsd.service.el.series.models

Class SeriesCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.axibase.tsd.service.el.series.models.SeriesCollection
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImmutableSeriesCollection

    public abstract class SeriesCollection
extends java.lang.Object
    Collection of series stored as a SortedMap: SeriesKey -> Series. Series are sorted by series key.
    Method naming convention:
    1. Functions like abs(), log() etc. are calculated for all samples of each series, and each series of the collection is transformed to series with the same key and the same set of timestamps.
    2. Method named as some statistical/aggregation function, e.g. sum(), median() etc., do calculations for each timestamp. So the function is calculated for the set of values with given timestamp from different series. Such methods return single series with default (mock) series key.
    3. Methods with prefix "series" apply statistical/aggregation function to each series in turn. These methods return collection of series with the same key.
    4. Methods with prefix "total" apply aggregation function to set of values with different timestamps and from all series. These methods generate either single double value or single regular series with default key.
    5. Methods with prefix "calculate" evaluate MVEL expression in specified contexts.
